reason: Zod schemas define all data types for patient profiles, trials, eligibility, and match results with runtime validation
description: TypeScript module with Zod schemas for PatientProfile, TrialDiscovery, EligibilityCriteria, MatchResult, and VoiceScript. Provides parse functions and type inference. Used by all agents and components for data validation at boundaries.

reason: Centralized configuration for all API keys and environment variables with validation
description: TypeScript module exporting validated environment configuration. Loads TOOLHOUSE_API_KEY, RTRVR_API_KEY, ELEVENLABS_API_KEY, STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY from environment. Provides getConfig() function with Zod validation for required keys.

reason: Toolhouse SDK wrapper for multi-agent orchestration with typed responses

functions.name: runAgent
functions.signature: (client: ToolhouseClient, agentId: string, input: unknown) => Promise<AgentResult>
functions.returns: Agent execution result with typed output

reason: rtrvr.ai API client for web scraping and data extraction from clinical trial pages

reason: ElevenLabs API client for text-to-speech synthesis with multi-language support

functions.name: synthesizeSpeech
functions.signature: (client: ElevenLabsClient, text: string, options: SpeechOptions) => Promise<AudioResult>

reason: Stripe client for payment checkout without backend server

context_urls.purpose: Stripe Payment Links for no-code checkout

reason: Geographic utilities for calculating distances between zipcodes using Haversine formula
description: TypeScript module for location-based filtering. Provides getCoordinates() to convert zipcode to lat/lng, calculateDistance() using Haversine formula, and filterByRadius() to filter trials within travel distance.

functions.name: getCoordinates
functions.signature: (zipcode: string) => { lat: number, lng: number } | null

functions.signature: (locations: Location[], origin: string, radiusMiles: number) => Location[]

reason: Agent 1 discovers actively recruiting clinical trials matching patient condition via ClinicalTrials.gov API
description: Clinical Trial Scout agent using Toolhouse orchestration. Queries ClinicalTrials.gov API v2.0 for recruiting interventional trials. Filters by condition, location, and phase. Returns up to 5 trial candidates with basic metadata. Uses rtrvr.ai for additional data extraction if needed.

functions.name: runScoutAgent
functions.returns: Array of up to 5 trial candidates

reason: Agent 2 extracts and parses eligibility criteria from trial pages into structured format
description: Eligibility Extractor agent using rtrvr.ai for web extraction. Parses inclusion/exclusion criteria from ClinicalTrials.gov trial pages. Categorizes criteria by type (diagnosis, biomarker, treatment, other). Returns structured eligibility JSON.

functions.name: runExtractorAgent
functions.returns: Structured eligibility criteria with categorized inclusion/exclusion

reason: Agent 3 compares patient profile against eligibility criteria to produce match scores
description: Clinical Matching Specialist agent. Compares patient profile fields against extracted eligibility criteria. Evaluates hard exclusions first, then inclusion alignment. Calculates weighted score (0-100) with category assignment (strong_match/possible_match/future_potential/not_eligible). Generates factor breakdown and plain-language summary.

functions.name: runMatcherAgent
functions.returns: Match score, category, factors, and summary

reason: Agent 4 generates compassionate voice scripts and synthesizes audio via ElevenLabs
description: Patient Advocate agent. Takes match results and generates plain-language voice script (8th-grade reading level). Includes encouraging tone, clear next steps, doctor consultation reminder, and required disclaimer. Synthesizes audio via ElevenLabs API. Supports multiple languages.

functions.name: runAdvocateAgent
functions.returns: Voice script text and audio URL

reason: Pipeline orchestrator coordinates all 4 agents in sequence with error handling
description: Main orchestrator module coordinating the multi-agent pipeline. Executes: Scout -> Extractor (parallel per trial) -> Matcher (parallel per trial) -> Advocate. Manages pipeline state, handles errors with graceful degradation, implements retry logic, and tracks execution progress for UI updates.

functions.name: runPipeline
functions.returns: Complete pipeline results with all match data and audio

reason: Patient intake form component with medical profile fields and validation
description: React component for patient data entry. Fields: diagnosis (text), stage (dropdown), biomarkers (text), ECOG score (0-4 dropdown), previous treatments (multi-select), zipcode (text), travel radius (slider), language preference (dropdown). Uses react-hook-form with Zod validation. Submits to orchestrator.

context_urls.purpose: React Hook Form with Zod validation

reason: Trial card component displays individual trial match with score and factors

reason: Pie chart component visualizes match category distribution across trials
description: React component using Recharts to display pie chart of match categories. Shows distribution of strong_match, possible_match, future_potential, and not_eligible. Color-coded segments with legend and counts.

reason: Audio player component for voice summary playback with transcript toggle
description: React component for playing ElevenLabs-generated audio. Shows play/pause button, progress bar, duration display. Includes transcript toggle for accessibility (hearing impaired). Displays voice script text when expanded.

reason: Progress indicator shows pipeline execution status with agent-level granularity

reason: Payment modal for Stripe checkout when user exceeds 5 free matches
